Make a web

Source: R/web_and_biadjacency.R
web.Rd

Generate a biadjacency matrix linking the features between two tables.

Usage

web(x, ...)

kegg_web(x, ...)

# Default S3 method
web(x, y, link = NULL, tableX = NULL, tableY = NULL, ...)

# S3 method for class 'formula'
web(formula, link = NULL, tableX = NULL, tableY = NULL, ...)

Arguments

x

name of feature type that will determine columns, corresponding to `tableX`.

...

further arguments to be passed to or from methods. Not used.

y

name of feature type that will determine rows, corresponding to `tableY`.

link

a data.frame with two columns, as named in x and y. Sharing a row indicates a link between features. See ec2ko and ec2cpd for examples. Optionally a list with two such data.frames.

tableX

A table containing features of interest. Rows should be samples and columns should be features. The Y and X refer to the position of the features in a formula: Y ~ X.

tableY

A table containing features of interest. Rows should be samples and columns should be features. The Y and X refer to the position of the features in a formula: Y ~ X.

formula

a formula of the form y ~ x, denoting desired output format; assigns y to rows and columns to x. Equivalent to using x and y arguments.

Value

a sparse binary biadjacency matrix, with features from y as rows and features from x as columns.

Examples

# Basic usage
web(x = "ko", y = "ec", link = ec2ko)

# A wrapper is available for kegg ko, ec and cpd data
generic      <- web(cpd ~ ko, link = list(ec2ko, ec2cpd))
kegg_wrapper <- kegg_web( cpd ~ ko )

identical(generic, kegg_wrapper)
#> [1] TRUE

# The following are equivalent to transposition:
a <- anansi:::get_dict( web(ko ~ cpd, link = list(ec2ko, ec2cpd)) )
b <- anansi:::get_dict( web(cpd ~ ko, link = list(ec2ko, ec2cpd)) )

identical(a, t(b))
#> [1] TRUE
